  "texts": [
    "Vapor-accumulating regions could be created, resulting in undesired thermal conditions and producing issues in the propellant removal.",
    "Moreover, the phenomena could be coupled with boiling induced by thermal superheat 26.",
    "These complex multiphase phenomena, including phase changes induced by pressure and temperature variations in microgravity conditions, are challenging to investigate experimentally and model 11.",
    "Validating different CFD and nodal tools with microgravity data is necessary to routinely design in-space cryogenic systems, especially with the fluid dynamics and heat transfer being tightly coupled as in two-phase cryogenic systems 20.",
    "One of the main difficulties arises because of the multiscale nature of the problem."
  ]
